. Some of the techniques used to cope with the temperature variations are well- known in the prior art. However, it does not appear to be obvious to combine them to come to the subject-matter claimed in claim 1. Especially the feature that the magnet strip can freely expand with respect to a base frame where it is attached to involves some non-obvious modifications to the prior art document D1. It is noted that D6 discloses similar features as D1.
2 Dependent claims 2-6.
Claims 2-6 are dependent on claim 1 and as such also meet the requirements of novelty and inventive step. Form NL237-3 (separate sheet) (July 2006) (sheet 3)
Certain defects in the application
The relevant background art disclosed in D1-D6 is not mentioned in the description, nor are these documents identified therein. Form NL237-3 (separate sheet) (July 2006) (sheet 4)
